http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Clean-up-drive/article13980642.ece

Involving a number of volunteers, Ken Foundation Society organised ‘Operation Red Hills-2016’ on Sunday. The annual endeavour was held at Erramatti Dibbalu where a number of students and employees from various colleges and organisations took part.Wearing protective gear, the team headed to the spot picking up plastic covers, papers and chunks of debris all along the path. More than 400 volunteers turned up for the clean-up drive. President of the foundation P. Santosh said that the initiative aims at protecting the ancient heritage site of the port city.